The paper deals with finding subgraphs in graphs, which is a topic in graph mining and community detection. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of exact algorithms and the study of algorithmic complexity suggest that the paper could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The focus on real-world graphs and empirical results suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
